dataIdInfo.idAbs: Park Boundary polygons for Acadia National Park, Maine. Use attributes to distinguish between lands in fee-ownership, lands still to be acquired in fee-ownership in accordance with Public Law 99-420 or Public Law 97-335 (inholdings or acquisition parcels), or conservation easements. Conservation easement lands held by the NPS are still in private ownership and are generally not open to public access; please observe landowner rights. NOTE: for official land status information, please contact the NPS Lands Office. This layer is produced, maintained, and used by Acadia National Park for cartographic purposes because it fits well with other local data. It does not represent an official or surveyed boundary and should not be used for land transaction purposes.
dataIdInfo.idPurp: To allow for cartography related to land holdings of the National Park Service at Acadia National Park in relation to local municipal parcel data.

report.measDesc:
Modifications to this layer were done with appropriate snapping conditions set and using map topology tools to try to avoid polygon overlaps or slivers between polygons. It is possible some of these errors exist in the data layer, however.
The attributes were very thoroughly proofed and edited in previous versions of this layer and are assumed to remain properly coded. Additions and changes that were made for this revision were confirmed with Acadia's Land Protection Specialist and double-checked for accuracy by viewing the layer and table in ArcMap10.x Parcel lines for the Northeast Creek area in this layer have been adjusted to to the shapes in the Bar Harbor tax parcels GIS layer. These shapes do not always agree with NPS survey/official land status map parcel shapes.

All lands included in the Congressionally legislated fee-ownership boundary are depicted by polygons; lands still to be acquired in fee-ownership (inholdings) are delineated separately to allow a map to only show current land holdings. In addition, conservation easements held by the NPS are included (less than fee-ownership). A final determination of boundary for the area around Northeast Creek was accepted in 2005; that outer boundary has been incorporated into this data layer, however the boundary may shift slightly as properties are actually acquired and surveyed. This layer should include all change orders issued by the Lands Office which have been communicated to Acadia NP staff through January 2018.

Parcel lines are considered estimates only and should not be used for transactions and/or legal descriptions, only for general depictions of land holdings. The primary purpose of this layer is cartography, which does not require precise locations, it just needs to fit with the other data layers. Most of the linework on Mount Desert Island originated from tablet-digitized town tax maps (multiple paper sheets, from 4 different towns, that were rubber-sheeted to fit each other, then adjusted to fit with 1:24000 DLG coastline and town line data layers), though some internal parcel lines had to be added from paper NPS land status maps. Tax parcel lines in Bar Harbor were re-done digitally in GIS by a town contractor and those lines have been incorporated into this data layer as of 2006. For all other areas (outside of Mount Desert Island), linework either comes from DLG park boundary layers and/or on-screen digitizing based on parcel survey maps and background GIS data layers. In the few cases where there was geo-reference on the NPS land status map (paper), the parcel lines may have been tablet digitized. Since approximately 2007, boundary re-survey/re-marking contracts have included a requirement to provide the surveyed line in GIS format; where those have become available, they have been incorporated into this data layer.

prcStep.stepDesc: Extracted parcels from LSM coded as CLASS2 = 'FEE' or 'AQU' to Temp1.shp. Dissolved internal parcel lines based on the value of CLASS2. Then selected all polygons and exploded multi-part features. Extracted parcels from LSM coded as CLASS2 = 'EAS' or 'EAS/AQU' to Temp2.shp; recoded 'EAS/AQU' to 'EAS' and dissolved internal parcel lines based on the value of CLASS2. Merged Temp1.shp and Temp2.shp. Modified attribute table to eliminate any useless fields. Used XTools to calculate the attributes Acres and Hectares. Updated metadata.
